Chakravyuh is a Bollywood political thriller directed by Prakash Jha starring Arjun Rampal, Abhay Deol, Manoj Bajpai, Kabir Bedi and Esha Gupta. Chakravyuh is aimed to be a social commentary on the issues of Naxalites and corrupt Communism.[2][3][4][5] Chakravyuh is still in its production phase, with the filming schedule to conclude around June 15th. The film is aiming a release sometime in November or December of 2012. A story of two friends (played by Arjun Rampal and Abhay Deol) on opposite sides of the same conflict - one fighting for the Naxalites and the other fighting against them.[6] Arjun Rampal plays the prototypical righteous, patriotic and good-intentioned police officer, SP Adil Khan, who finds himself in a critical dilemma in the city of Bhopal, overwrought with Naxalite rioters and seedy underworld terrorists.[7] Music for this film is composed by Shankar-Ehsaan-Loy.There is item song Tambai rang tera Paro in the film,choreographed by Ganesh Acharya.[15]
